# Telegram Reports

How and when to send a report to {{ operator_name }} via `mc telegram`.

## When to send

- The task produced a result relevant to {{ operator_name }} (research output, deploy
  finished, artifact delivered, recommendation)
- The task failed or is partial and {{ operator_name }} should know why
- **BEFORE `mc finish`** — one report per task completion

**MANDATORY when `report_back_required=true`:** the backend hard-gates `mc finish`
with 422 if you haven't sent `mc telegram` first.

**MANDATORY for file deliverables** (PDF/Excel/Word/image): the report MUST attach
the file:
- `mc telegram "<text>" --file <deliverable_id>` (document, sendDocument)
- `mc telegram "<caption>" --photo <deliverable_id>` (image, sendPhoto)

`deliverable_id` comes from the `mc pdf` response or `mc deliverable --type file`.
Text-only `mc telegram` on file tasks is a bug — {{ operator_name }} should see the
file directly in Telegram, not go hunting in the UI.

## When NOT to send

- Intermediate status / progress pings → `mc comment progress` instead
- **You're working on a subtask** (`parent_task_id` is set) — no `mc telegram`.
  The orchestrator consolidates and sends the final report. The backend enforces
  this with 422 "Subtask cannot send Telegram". Exception: `autonomous_telegram=true`
  in the brief (long-running watch tasks).

## Format (HTML)

```
<agent-emoji> <AgentName> · <Short Title> <Status-Emoji>

<One-sentence summary>

─────────────────

<Sub-Emoji> <b>Section</b>
• Point

⏱️ <Duration> · 📄 Task <short-id>
```

Allowed HTML tags: `<b>`, `<i>`, `<code>`, `<a href="...">`. No `<div>`/styles —
Telegram strips them. No `TELEGRAMSTART`/`===`/`EOF` delimiters — heredoc content
goes 1:1 into the message.

## Usage

```bash
mc telegram "<complete message as one string>"

mc telegram - <<'EOF'
🔍 Researcher · …
…
EOF

mc telegram "Caption" --photo <deliverable-uuid>
mc telegram "Report — file attached" --file <deliverable-uuid>
```

## Fallback discipline

If `mc telegram` unexpectedly fails: `mc telegram --help` first, then `mc help
<agent>`, then `mc question`. Only after that: raw API call — but check
`deliverable_id` (screenshots) vs `document_deliverable_id` (PDF/Office) in the
backend schema first.
